description:
&lt;p&gt;Norfolk and Suffolk NHS Foundation Trust are recruiting an Investigation and Improvement Manager (IIM) to further complement the Patient Safety Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The IIM will take the lead in investigating allocated serious incidents on behalf of the Trust. The post holder will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Conduct thorough investigations into serious incidents, as necessary, using appropriate methodologies, whilst ensuring that the principles of Being Open are applied.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Draft complex reports outlining the findings of investigations and compile robust action plans in conjunction with the appropriate local managers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contribute to the development, application, monitoring and review of serious incidents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support the Patient Safety Team in the process of analysing and embedding learning across the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits included with this role are:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a comprehensive in house &amp; external training programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;career progression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;starting annual leave of 27 days per annum increasing to 33 days pa based on length of service (plus paid bank holidays)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;staff physio service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts and many more.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here at NSFT we pride ourselves on being a welcoming, talented, friendly and supportive te&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please find attached our Job Description and Person Specification for more detail on your Key Accountabilities, then if you feel you have what it takes to make a difference in your local communities, click APPLY!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview date is yet to be confirmed, candidates may only be given a minimum of 3 days’ notice, please note this date is provisional and may be subject to change. You will be contacted via email and invited to book a time. These emails may go to your SPAM, so please keep checking all your emails if applying.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
